						<p class="faqquestion">{{{__ 'NEW MEXICAN CUISINE'}}}</p>
						<p>{{{__ 'When it comes to restaurants, Santa Fe has an embarrassment of riches. Here are some tips for anyone new to New Mexican cooking:'}}}</p>
						<ul>
							<li>{{{__ 'You\'ll find chile all over menus, in everything from enchiladas to ice cream.'}}}</li>
							<li>{{{__ 'Chile comes in green and red, and is typically served as a sauce. Not sure of the heat level? Just ask your server.'}}}</li>
							<li>{{{__ 'Sopapillas, another local staple, are a Native American fried dough served with honey.'}}}</li>
							<li>{{{__ 'Posole is a chile and pork stew served with hominy.'}}}</li>
						</ul><br/>
						<img src="/img/posole.jpg" alt="Posole" style="display: block; max-width: 250px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" /><br /><br />
						<p class="faqquestion">{{{__ 'OUR FAVORITE RESTAURANTS'}}}</p>
						<ul>
							<li><a
				      href="https://www.facebook.com/Clafoutis-250750308289765/" target="_blank"><strong>Clafoutis</strong></a>: {{{__ 'A French cafe and bakery, with delicious freshly made beignets only available on Saturdays.'}}}</li>
							<li><a
				      href="https://www.facebook.com/Counter-Culture-Cafe-152108598154559/" target="_blank"><strong>Counter Culture</strong></a>: {{{__ 'Don\'t miss their huge homemade cinnamon rolls, only available Wednesday, Saturday, and Sunday. They also serve soup and sandwiches.'}}}</li>
							<li><a
				      href="http://iconikcoffee.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Iconik Coffee</strong></a>: {{{__ 'Minimal food options, but tasty coffee.'}}}</li>
							<li><a
				      href="http://www.pantrysantafe.com/" target="_blank"><strong>The Pantry</strong></a>: {{{__ 'There\'s always a line, but this is our favorite for quintessential New Mexican dishes.'}}}</li>
							<li><a
				      href="https://www.yelp.com/biz/el-chile-toreado-santa-fe" target="_blank"><strong>El Chile Toreado</strong></a>: {{{__ 'Stop by this food truck for spicy, flavorful, and pretty damn amazing burritos and tacos. Open for breakfast and lunch only.'}}}</li>
							<li><a
				      href="http://the-shed-restaurant.myshopify.com/" target="_blank"><strong>The Shed</strong></a>: {{{__ 'A Santa Fe institution, known for having the best chile (which you can also buy by the jar). Prepare to wait in line, or grab a spot at the bar and sip one of their margaritas. They also serve breakfast.'}}}</li>
							<li><a
				      href="http://www.tiasophias.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Tia Sophia's</strong></a>: {{{__ 'Famous sopapillas and New Mexican home cooking (just FYI, the sopapillas are only served at lunch, not breakfast). For a hearty breakfast with a spicy kick, order the breakfast burrito with "Christmas" (red and green) chile.'}}}</li>
							<li><a
				      href="http://tomasitas.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Tomasita's</strong></a>: {{{__ 'Classic New Mexican fare, with vegetarian and gluten-free options.'}}}</li>
							<li><a
				      href="https://sagebakehouse.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Sage Bakehouse</strong></a>: {{{__ 'Fabulous freshly made bread and delicious sandwiches. Bonus: Sage is across the street from our wedding hotel!'}}}</li>
							<li><a
				      href="http://paper-dosa.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Paper Dosa</strong></a>: {{{__ 'Beautiful ambiance and wonderful Southern Indian fare. Be sure to try their salted lemonade.'}}}</li>
							<li><a
				      href="http://jambocafe.net/" target="_blank"><strong>Jambo</strong></a>: {{{__ 'Worth the short trek out of town, and don\'t be fooled by the strip mall facade. A local favorite serving a mix of Swahili, Indian, Arabic, and European influenced cuisine, and they have the best chai in town. Vegetarian, vegan, and gluten-free dishes available.'}}}</li>
							<li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/The-Bonsai-ASIAN-TACOS-856098811080327/" target="_blank"><strong>Bonsai Asian Tacos</strong></a>: {{{__ 'Another food truck, this time serving Asian tacos (picture Bulgogi meat, ginger, guacamole, jicama... yum). Open for a late breakfast, lunch, and dinner.'}}}</li>
							<li><a href="http://www.vinaigretteonline.com/santafe_menu" target="_blank"><strong>Vinaigrette</strong></a>: {{{__ 'Twenty different salads, plus sandwiches and soups. Vegetarian, vegan, and gluten-free options. Open for lunch and dinner.'}}}</li>
						  <li><a href="http://www.sazonsantafe.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Sazon</strong></a>: {{{__ 'Check out their cozy bar and delicious cocktails.'}}}</li>
						  <li><a href="http://radishandrye.com/#farminspiredcuisine" target="_blank"><strong>Radish &amp; Rye</strong></a>: {{{__ 'Small plates and craft cocktails. Pricey but worth it if you\'re in the mood to splurge.'}}}</li>
						  <li><a href="http://www.labocasantafe.com/" target="_blank"><strong>La Boca</strong></a>: {{{__ 'Spanish tapas with a nice selection of Mediterranean and South American wines.'}}}</li>
						  <li><a href="http://www.sweetwatersf.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Sweetwater Harvest Kitchen</strong></a>: {{{__ 'Locally sourced ingredients and lots of vegetarian, vegan, and gluten-free options. Try their Thai Nights on Wednesday through Saturday evenings.'}}}</li>
						  <li><a href="http://tuneupsantafe.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Tune-up Cafe</strong></a>: {{{__ 'The El Salvadorian papusas are a must-try at this family-friendly cafe. A great local hang-out with cozy ambiance.'}}}</li>
						</ul><br/>

